TikTok is calling on all South Africans to unite through song and dance by participating in the #MzansiDance challenge on the platform tomorrow, which is Heritage Day. They have also created a MzansiDance Playlist which users can make use of in their videos. Locals are urged to take on the broad range of dancing styles including Tolatsa, Vosho, Pantsula, Two-step, Pouncing Cat, Ngwazi, Gwara Gwara, and so many more, which all capture the vibrant energy of the country and its people. South African Rugby Captain, Siya Kolisi, has already joined the challenge and has encouraged users to duet with him. Here is his duet here with local creator, Tebza Diphehlo:   Somaya Stockenstroom